04628nam a22006375i 9780520353626DE-B159720240306123113.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||240306t19971997cau    fo  d z      eng d  a97805203536267 a10.1525/97805203536262doi  a(DE-B1597)648110  a(OCoLC)1419789057  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  acaucUS-CA 7aHIS0100102bisacsh1 aMertus/Tesanovic, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aSuitcase :bRefugee Voices from Bosnia and Croatia /cMertus/Tesanovic; ed. by Rada Boric, Jasmina Tesanovic, Julie A. Mertus, Habiba Metikos. 1aBerkeley, CA : bUniversity of California Press, c[1997] 4c©1997  a1 online resource (267 p.) :b20 photos.  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tCONTENTS -- tACKNOWLEDGMENTS -- tFOREWORD -- tINTRODUCTION -- tTHE SUITCASE -- tThe Journey Out -- tDreams of Home -- tEveryday Refugee Life -- tChildren's Voices -- tStarting Life Anew -- tAFTERWORDS -- tThe ABCs of Exile -- tThe Face of Women Refugees from Muslim Communities: Algeria to Ex-Yugoslavia -- tBeyond the Balkans -- tPOSTSCRIPT -- tThis Is Not War Talk -- tNOTES ON CONTRIBUTORS0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThe whirlwind of Europe's longest war in half a century has produced this powerful collection of personal narratives—essays, letters, and poems—from refugees fleeing Bosnia and Croatia. Taking us behind the barrage of media coverage, these stories tell of perseverance, brutality, forced departure, exile, and courage. With startling immediacy and in moving detail, speakers tell of stuffing a few belongings—a handful of photographs, a rock from the garden, a change of clothes—into a suitcase and fleeing their homeland.Contributors from all ethnic groups and every region of Bosnia and Croatia describe their sense of lost community, memories of those left behind, recollections of town squares that no longer exist, and homes now occupied by neighbors. The editors of The Suitcase, themselves representing the diverse peoples of the region, traveled to camps and temporary homes across the globe to collect these stories. An antidote to apathy, this work moves beyond and outside the vicissitudes of daily politics to portray the human tragedy at the center of present-day Bosnia and Croatia. Probing the intimate losses of countless individuals, it delivers a powerful indictment of injustice, militarism, prejudice, and warfare.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aEastern. 4aEurope. 4aHistory. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Eastern.2bisacsh1 aBoric, Rada, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHelie-Lucas, Marieme, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMayotte, Judith, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMertus, Julie A., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMertus, Julie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMetikos, Habiba, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aTesanovic, Jasmina, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aUgresic, Dubravka, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWest, Cornel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000z97831106353480 cprintz978052020634240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052035362640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520353626423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520353626/original  a978-3-11-063534-8  University of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alle